===Retired numbers===
[[Image:PA101101.jpg|thumb|Retired numbers at Turner Field]]
{{See also|List of Major League Baseball retired numbers}}

The Braves have retired eight numbers in the history of the franchise, including most recently Greg Maddux's number 31 in 2009 and Tom Glavine's number 47 in 2010. Additionally, Hank Aaron's 44, and Jackie Robinson's 42, which is retired for all of baseball with the exception of Yankees' closer Mariano Rivera and Jackie Robinson Day&lt;ref&gt;Araton, Harvey (14 April 2010). [http://www.nytimes.com/2010/04/15/sports/baseball/15rivera.html?_r=1 &quot;Yankees' Mariano Rivera is the last No. 42.&quot;] ''The New York Times''. Retrieved June 9, 2010.&lt;/ref&gt;, have also been retired.

On March 22, 2011 the Braves announced that [[Bobby Cox]] will be inducted into the Atlanta Braves Hall of Fame and have his number six retired at a luncheon on August 12, 2011. Afterward, an on-field ceremony will be held to recognize the long-time Braves manager before the scheduled game versus the [[2011 Chicago Cubs season|Chicago Cubs]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://atlanta.braves.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20110322&amp;content_id=17058046&amp;vkey=news_atl&amp;c_id=atl|title=Braves to retire Cox's No. 6, add him to Hall|work=atlantabraves.com|date=22 March 2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;

As displayed at Turner Field:

