      <text xml:space="preserve">'''ABCD''' is a list of the first four letters in the [[English alphabet]].  It may also refer to:

==In medicine==

* [[ABC (medicine)]], also known as ABCD, a mnemonic for steps in resuscitation
* [[ABCD rating]], a staging system for prostate cancer
* [[ABCD syndrome]], a genetic disorder
* [[ABCD guideline]], a heuristic for detecting melanomas
* [[ABCD² score]], a score for determining the risk of stroke after TIA

==In science==
* [[ABCD matrix analysis]], a type of ray tracing technique used in the design of some optical systems
* [[ABCD-parameters]], a type of properties describing the electrical behavior of linear electrical networks

==In non-profits==
* [[Action for Boston Community Development, Inc. (ABCD)]], a Boston, Massachsuetts based non-profit social services agency

==In other fields==
* [[CompTIA]], also known as the Association of Better Computer Dealers
* [[ABCD Region]], an industrial district outside of São Paulo, Brazil
* [[American-Born Confused Desi]], refers to American youth of South Asian descent
** [[ABCD (2005 film)|''ABCD'' (2005 film)]], film about growing up in New York as a first or second generation South Asian American
* [[Asset-based community development]], a methodology that seeks to uncover and highlight the strengths within communities
* [[USS Atlanta (1884)|USS ''Atlanta'' (1884)]], [[USS Boston (1884)|USS ''Boston'' (1884)]], [[USS Chicago (1885)|USS ''Chicago'' (1885)]], and [[USS Dolphin (PG-24)|USS ''Dolphin'' (PG-24)]], the first four steel ships built during the &quot;New Navy&quot; period of U.S. Naval history
* ABCD: add, browse, change, delete, another representation of [[Create, read, update and delete]]
* American, British, Chinese, and Dutch, the main powers opposing the Empire of Japan before the [[Pacific War]] in World War II
* [[Archer Daniels Midland]], [[Bunge Limited|Bunge]], [[Cargill]], and [[Louis Dreyfus Group|Louis Dreyfus]], four major agriculture commodity companies

== blue links ==
